Searching means finding whether an element exists in the array.

Linear Search

Find the index of a target element in an array by checking each element one by one.

Example: 

Input:
arr = [4, 7, 1, 9]
target = 7

Output:
1
Because 7 is at index 1.

arr = [4,7,1,9]
target = 7

for i in range(len(arr)):
    if arr[i] == target:
        print(i)
        break
